; Regression test for issue #1602: Problem with "N" command (BZ#530)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1602
;
; The N directive is supposed to mark a commodity as non-market, meaning
; it should be excluded from market-price valuations (-V/-X). However,
; the flag is not checked in amount_t::value(), so price conversion still
; occurs even when N is set for the commodity.
;
; Correct behavior: N ACME should prevent -V from converting ACME via
; price database. The balance should remain as ACME, not be converted to $.
; Current (broken) behavior: -V still converts ACME to $ using pricedb.

N ACME

P 2020/06/01 ACME $75.00

2020/01/01 Buy ACME
    Assets:Investments   10 ACME @ $50.00
    Assets:Cash

test bal -V
             $250.00  Assets
            $-500.00    Cash
             $750.00    Investments
--------------------
             $250.00
end test
